org.dataconservancy.packaging.tool.ser

Class AbstractPackageToolConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dataconservancy.packaging.tool.ser.AbstractPackageToolConverter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.Converter, com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.ConverterMatcher
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ApplicationVersionConverter, DomainProfileUriListConverter, PackageMetadataConverter, PackageNameConverter, UserPropertyConverter

    public abstract class AbstractPackageToolConverter
extends Object
implements com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.Converter
    Abstract XStream converter for Package Tool GUI serialization. Any XStream converters are expected to inherit from this class.

    This converter is responsible for encapsulating all XStream serializations with serialization metadata, and providing access to the metadata to sub classes via the marshalling contexts MarshallingContext and UnmarshallingContext. The metadata include:

    version - context key version, context value Integer (since version 1)
    an integer indicating the version of the serialization format
    converterClass - context key A_CONVERTER_CLASS, context value String (since version 1)
    fully qualified name of the Java class that produced the serialization
    stream identifier context key A_STREAMID, context value StreamId (since version 1)
    symbolic name identifying the serialized stream

    Additional metadata can be added in the future. Metadata documentation should include the field name and the version that the metadata was added. Metadata are meant to enable forward compatability of the serializations consumed and produced by this converter. Future versions of the Package Tool GUI should be able to read serializations produced by previous versions.
